metadata.name: It came from the stars #24
metadata.description:
"It is said that long ago, the Greater Will sent a golden star bearing a beast into the Lands Between ..."

Fully procedural beast and environment, everything generated at runtime.
A love letter to FromSoftware.

Don't hesitate to use the camera controls to view the beasts.

More informations on the generator's origins and how it is made available at : https://ulucode.com/wp/it-came-from-the-stars/

Controls:
Press space to open/close a menu.
Mouse Left   : Rotate
Mouse Right  : Pan
Mouse Middle : Dolly/zoom

Capture & Exports :
Export size depends on your browser window size. Choose a multiplier and press the button. If the capture doesn't work, try a smaller multiplier.

Warning: This piece is GPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices. Chrome very recommended

Additional controls:
Press "a" to alternate between different anti-aliasing intensity. Warning : GPU intensive
Press "s" to check some stats

Menu font is EB Garamond
Powered by three.js
NFT License

metadata.name: Provence #334
metadata.description:
The south of France namely the Provence has a cultural history of being an inspiration for impressionists and post-impressionists in the past.
For me personally the Provence is the place i was spending long, peaceful holidays as a child within beautiful nature.
This work does not so much aim for being realistic, rather than give an impression or feeling for this wonderful landscape. 
There are just a few different elements and concepts and yet there is variety of fascinating results.
I really hope you will enjoy your minting.

Notes:
STARTUP AND RENDERING MAY TAKE SOME TIME. (Up to 1min)
Code was written in typescript.
The only used libraries were chroma.js and simplex-noise

metadata.name: Rebug #531
metadata.description:
A debug view of the underlying particulate algorithm of Atoms' Gaze and Quantum Folly. Refined as a gift for collectors.

Enjoy watching the structures form. Once it's fully rendered you can download a full resolution image of 3508 x 4961 px by ***double clicking/tapping***. At this size the piece is printable at A3 size at 300 dpi. If you're interested in acquiring a signed print please contact @KRANKARTA.

Created on Chrome desktop 103.0 on 2022-08-06 in javascript and GLSL. Results on other browsers/devices may vary.

metadata.name: Living City #6
metadata.description:
It is a "Living City"

The state of the city sky will change by receiving your current time.
For example, if it is morning in your city, the sun will rise in your mint, and if it is night, your mint will be dark.

The settings are such that at 06:00 in your geographical area, the sun rises and the sky slowly brightens, and at 19:00 in your geographical area, the sky darkens and the sun sets. In the rest of the night, the moon will shine in the sky and the position of the moon in the sky will change every hour of the night.

To see this effect better, you can take a photo of each watch and compare the photos.

- Press â€œsâ€ to save the current canvas.

* Note: If it is night in your geographical location, you will definitely see the minted pieces with a dark sky with the moon, and if it is day, you will see a bright sky with a random background color with the sun.

--
Artist: Pointiago
Aug 02, 2022
License: NFT 2.0

metadata.name: blinksquare 2022 #88
metadata.description:
From the pixel-lab vault - evolved from 'blinksquare' (2008) 
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Mouse-click switches between:
- screen scaled image
- The large image (for printing)

Right-click: Save/Copy the image

A custom created 'soft' pixel 2D/3D engine,
written in vanilla JavaScript some more info in the source-code
- The work will refresh and restart after some time -
-------------------------------------------------

I created 'blinksquare' back in 2008 in Secondlife,
it was like a kinetic 3D sculpture; that would change over time.

I wanted to do a 2022 remake; and while working on it; it evolved a bit.
Also inspired by writing and ancient Hieroglyphs from around the world 


xxx Amsterdam chillout


For the love of Art, hugging someone you love, and filling that RGB-and Z buffer  ^__^
